ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes I would recommend the course
One of the better environmental engineering courses I've taken
Yes, I strongly recommend this course to other students.

This class is an overview of different environmental processes. It's purpose is to introduce you to the underlying fundamentals, but not to go in depth into the design of a full system. It will also introduce you to relevant current research for each process.I would recommend this to a fellow student who does not have an environmental engineering background.
An important course for any environmental engineer. Helps you develop a fundamental understanding of many important treatment processes.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned a lot of useful information that all environmental engineers should know.
I have stronger understanding of fundamental processes in environmental engineering processes, some of which are involved in my research.
